been这个been有的一讲
Snowball also threw 
on to the fire the ribbons with which the horses’ manes and tails 
had usually been decorated on market days. 
had usually been decorated 这里been是因为在这句话中动词是decorated，在英语中“一句话只能有一个谓语动词”,又因为这句话的主语马的鬓毛和尾巴的装饰只能被动的被认为装饰，所以被动句的过去完成时是had been decorated.

Ribbons,” he said, “should be considered as clothes, which are the 
mark of a human being. All animals should go naked.”
